          "title": "Common Errors",
          "content": "<Section>\n\n#### 1. The command docker couldn't be found in this WSL 2  Distro.\n> ERROR:  You don't have any WSL2 Distro, Please convert a WSL 1 Distro to WSL 2 , or install a new distro and it will appear here.\n\n<SubSection>\n\nThis Happens if you have installed Ubuntu without running the below command:\n\nRun the below command in powershell:\n\n```powershell\nwsl --set-default-version 2\n```\n\n</SubSection>\n\n#### 2.The command 'docker couldn't be found in this WSL 1  Distro.(set wsl 2 as default) or WSL Integration\n\n<SubSection>\nThis happens if you missed didn't Enable Docker Integration with the WSL.\n\n`Open Docker Desktop Application >> Resources >> WSL Integration, then Enable WSL Integration`.\n</SubSection>\n\n#### 3. DockerException: Error while fetching server API version.\n>ERROR:  docker.errors.DockerException: Error while fetching server API version: ('Connection aborted.', FileNotFoundError(2, 'No such file or directory'))\n\n![Getting Started](https://res.cloudinary.com/learning-platform/image/fetch/dpr_auto,w_auto,f_auto,q_auto/https://nkb-backend-ccbp-media-static.s3.ap-south-1.amazonaws.com/prod/media/profile_pic/card-notes-attachment/8288c6f9-a589-4628-9a03-264dcc98fa01.png)\n\n<SubSection>\nThis happens if Docker Desktop is not running. Please start/restart Docker Desktop, wait for it to completely start, and try running these commands again.\n</SubSection>\n\n#### 4. While opening the localhost Docker getting started page is opening\n\n[](https://nkb-backend-ccbp-media-static.s3.ap-south-1.amazonaws.com/otg_prod/media/discussion_attachment/6132f655-df94-4dd9-a419-38ad96965e6b)\n\n<SubSection>\nThis could be a cache issue, so clear all cookies and cache of the browser.\n\nIf the issue still persists Open the http://localhost in the incognito window.\n</SubSection>\n\n\n#### 5. Unable to start CCBP-IDE: Ports are not available.\n> ERROR: Ports are not available: listen tcp 0.0.0.0:PORT ...\n\n<SubSection>\nPlease go through the below discussion:\n\n[https://learning.ccbp.in/discussions/245aec94-9906-4142-ab49-02647e7ba8ca](https://learning.ccbp.in/discussions/245aec94-9906-4142-ab49-02647e7ba8ca)\n\nIf the solutions mentioned in above discussion didn't resolve your issue, follow below steps:\n\n- Open Powershell as Administrator.\n- Run the below command to check which process is running on port, replace *\\<PORT>* with port number on which you're facing the issue:\n\n```powershell\nnetstat -aon | findstr <PORT>\n```\n\n- Kill the process by using the below command, replace the *\\<PID>* with the number you got next to the LISTENING:\n\n```powershell\ntaskkill /f /pid <PID>\n```\n\n</SubSection>\n\n#### 6. dial tcp: timeout\n> ERROR: dial tcp: lookup auth.docker.io on 192.x.x.x:x read udp 192.x.x.x:x->192.x.x.x:x: i/o timeout\n\n![Dial Tcp Timeout](https://res.cloudinary.com/learning-platform/image/fetch/dpr_auto,w_auto,f_auto,q_auto/https%3A%2F%2Fnkb-backend-ccbp-media-static.s3.ap-south-1.amazonaws.com%2Fotg_prod%2Fmedia%2Fdiscussion_attachment%2F76b72275-b79a-444b-88fd-44531456e8b2.jpeg)\n\n<SubSection>\nThe download is being interrupted. This happens due to an unstable internet connection.\n\nRe-running the last command until the download completes is the only way to get through this.\n</SubSection>\n\n</Section>"
