        "instructions": "# 2. System Requirements\n\nThe following hardware prerequisites are required to successfully setup **CCBP IDE** in your **Mac System**\n\n- **Mac hardware must be a 2010 or a newer model with an Intel processor**, with Intel\u2019s hardware support for memory management unit (MMU) virtualization, including Extended Page Tables (EPT) and Unrestricted Mode.\n\n    - You can check to see if your machine has this support by running the following command in a terminal\n\n    ```sh\n    sysctl kern.hv_support\n    ```\n\n    - If your Mac supports the Hypervisor framework, the command prints\n\n    ```text\n    kern.hv_support: 1\n    ```\n\n- **macOS must be version 10.14 or newer**. That is, Mojave, Catalina, or Big Sur. We recommend upgrading to the latest version of macOS.\n\n- At least 4GB of RAM\n\n<MultiLineNote>\nFor smooth running of the IDE, it is recommended to have **8 GB of RAM** and an **SSD**. With a lesser configuration, you will experience your Mac to hang occasionally as the setup is Memory and Disk intensive.\n</MultiLineNote>\n<MultiLineNote>\nOlder versions of VirtualBox (prior to version 4.3.30) must not be installed.\n</MultiLineNote>\n\n<MultiLineWarning>\nIf your PC date & time are incorrect, then you will run into issues during installation and usage. You need to update your PC's date & time and *restart* it before proceeding further.\n</MultiLineWarning>\n\n",
